import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('Year').count().reset_index()
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Entity', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Natural Disasters')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="Entity", y="Deaths", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Natural Disaster Type', ylabel='Total Number of Deaths')
    ax.axhline(y=data['Deaths'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Deaths: {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].max()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Deaths', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Deaths'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Number of Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths resulting from natural disasters?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Deaths'])]
    data = data.groupby(['Year']).mean().reset_index()
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['Deaths'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average number of deaths')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average number of deaths')
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths resulting from natural disasters per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x="Entity", y="Deaths", data=data, hue="Entity", palette="Set2")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of deaths and the type of natural disaster?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
